1 6. In sending a mail ballot to an active registered voter,
2 the county clerk shall use an envelope that may not be
3 forwarded to an address of the voter that is different from
4 the address to which the mail ballot is mailed.
5 7. The return envelope must include postage prepaid by
6 first-class mail if the active registered voter is within the
7 boundaries of the United States, its territories or possessions
8 or on a military base.
9 And be it further
10 RESOLVED, That a new section, designated Section 12, be added
11 to Article 2 of the Nevada Constitution to read as follows:
12 Sec. 12. 1. Any polling place that is used for early
13 voting by personal appearance or for voting in person on
14 the day of the election must accept the submission of mail
15 ballots by voters while voting in person occurs.
16 2. During the 3 days immediately preceding any
17 primary or general election, each county clerk shall
18 establish sites in accordance with subsection 3 at which
19 voters may return mail ballots. Any site established
20 pursuant to this subsection must be available for at least 8
21 hours on each day and located at a polling place that is used
22 for early voting by personal appearance or voting in person
23 on the day of the election.
24 3. For the purposes of subsection 2, a county clerk
25 shall establish:
26 (a) In a county whose population is 700,000 or more, at
27 least 10 sites which meet the requirements of subsection 2.
28 (b) In a county whose population is 100,000 or more but
29 less than 700,000, at least 5 sites which meet the
30 requirements of subsection 2.
31 (c) In a county whose population is less than 100,000, at
32 least 1 site which meets the requirements of subsection 2.
33 4. A county clerk may, in addition to the sites
34 established pursuant to this section, provide any additional
35 number of sites which meet the requirements of
36 subsection 2.
37 5. The Legislature may provide by law for increasing
38 the required number of sites established pursuant to this
39 section.
40 And be it further
41 RESOLVED, That this resolution becomes effective upon
42 passage.
